********************************************************

HTTP - Hyper Text Transfer Protocol

********************************************************

It is a stateless protocol

For Ubuntu linux distribution Apache HTTP server is availbale to install and run HTTP server

Apache HTTP server is basically a file server. It can not implement any logic. 
It can just only transfer the files. 

HTTP uses the port 80 [Generally]

Some helpful linux commands.


Apache2
-------
	To install apache2 run below command.
	$sudo apt-get install apache2	//This will download apache package and install on machine.

	To check if apache web server is running or not, run below command.
	$systemctl status apache2

	To start apache server, run below command 
	$sudo systemctl start apache2
	 
